<ul>
  <li>I was wrong when I wrote: <a href="http://rolandtanglao.com/2018/09/09/p1-still-cannot-launch-firefox-from-wsl-without-lots-of-yakshaving/">Still can’t launch Firefox from Windows Subystem From Linux without a Selenium server and some hacks that nobody has working (Chrome works though)</a> back on September 9, 2018.</li>
  <li>It’s easy to use the <code class="highlighter-rouge">Launchy</code> ruby gem</li>
  <li>Just set the <code class="highlighter-rouge">BROWSER</code> enviroment variable and the Launchy just works:</li>
